cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the efficiency of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) in solving sequential data problems. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the properties of RNNs. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RNNs are a popular tool in AI research. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as RNNs are often used in natural language processing tasks. Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as RNNs are also used in image and video analysis.
